<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" ><generator uri="https://jekyllrb.com/" version="3.9.0">Jekyll</generator><link href="http://localhost:4000/feed.xml" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /><link href="http://localhost:4000/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><updated>2021-01-28T14:17:24-05:00</updated><id>http://localhost:4000/feed.xml</id><title type="html">Fresh Cargo</title><subtitle>YATB: Yet another technology blog</subtitle><entry><title type="html">Production Airflow Server in Five Minutes</title><link href="http://localhost:4000/airflow/devops/packer/2021/01/21/production-airflow-in-five-minutes.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Production Airflow Server in Five Minutes" /><published>2021-01-21T19:43:29-05:00</published><updated>2021-01-21T19:43:29-05:00</updated><id>http://localhost:4000/airflow/devops/packer/2021/01/21/production-airflow-in-five-minutes</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://localhost:4000/airflow/devops/packer/2021/01/21/production-airflow-in-five-minutes.html">&lt;p&gt;This guide will help you get a production-ready Airflow server up-and-running from scratch in just a few minutes. The only dependency is Packer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;“From scratch” means that we will start with nothing more than Packer and the files in &lt;a href=&quot;&quot;&gt;this Github repo&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It follows the guide published &lt;a href=&quot;https://airflow.apache.org/docs/apache-airflow/stable/installation.html&quot;&gt;on the Airflow web site&lt;/a&gt;. That guide is a great start but it leaves out the information you need to really start from scratch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-bash&quot; data-lang=&quot;bash&quot;&gt;packer build &lt;span class=&quot;nt&quot;&gt;-on-error&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;abort &lt;span class=&quot;nt&quot;&gt;-force&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nt&quot;&gt;-var-file&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;./variables.json ubuntu-18.json&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;</content><author><name></name></author><category term="airflow" /><category term="devops" /><category term="packer" /><summary type="html">This guide will help you get a production-ready Airflow server up-and-running from scratch in just a few minutes. The only dependency is Packer.</summary></entry></feed>